# ORBIT Brand Style Guide Compliance Rules

## MANDATORY STYLE GUIDE REFERENCE

**CRITICAL**: Before making ANY design, styling, or UI decisions, you MUST:
1. Read and reference `ORBIT_STYLE_GUIDE.md`
2. Follow all guidelines specified in the style guide
3. Cite relevant sections when making design choices

The `ORBIT_STYLE_GUIDE.md` file is the **single source of truth** for all brand design decisions.

---

## TYPOGRAPHY RULES (STRICTLY ENFORCED)

### English Text (All Elements)
- **MUST ALWAYS** use `Gotham` font family for ALL English text
- **MUST ALWAYS** use `font-heading`, `font-gotham`, or default `sans` (which is Gotham)
- **MUST ALWAYS** use Gotham for headings (h1-h6), body text, buttons, UI elements
- **NEVER** use Botera, Montserrat, or any other font for English text
- **NEVER** use custom fonts outside Gotham (English) and Somar (Arabic)

**Correct:**
```jsx
<h1 className="font-heading text-4xl">Title</h1>
<h2 className="font-gotham text-3xl">Section</h2>
<p className="font-gotham">Body text</p>
<p>Body text</p> // ✅ OK - default sans is Gotham
<button className="font-gotham">Button</button>
```

**Incorrect:**
```jsx
<h1 className="font-botera text-4xl">Title</h1> // ❌ WRONG - Botera was example only
<p className="font-montserrat">Body text</p> // ❌ WRONG - Montserrat was example only
```

### Arabic/RTL Text
- **MUST ALWAYS** use `Somar` font family for ALL Arabic/RTL text
- **MUST ALWAYS** use `font-somar` Tailwind class
- **NEVER** use Tajawal or any other font for Arabic text
- **NEVER** use Gotham for Arabic content

**Correct:**
```jsx
<p className="font-somar" dir="rtl">النص العربي</p>
```

**Incorrect:**
```jsx
<p className="font-tajawal" dir="rtl">النص العربي</p> // ❌ WRONG
```

---

## COLOR RULES (STRICTLY ENFORCED)

### Brand Colors Only
- **MUST ALWAYS** use ORBIT brand colors from the style guide:
  - **Primary (Burgundy)**: `bg-primary`, `text-primary` (`#7A1E2E`)
  - **Secondary (Beige)**: `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary` (`#E8DCCB`)
  - **Neutral (Cool Gray)**: `bg-neutral`, `text-neutral` (`#A7A9AC`)
  - **Black**: `#161616` (ORBIT Black)
  - **White**: `#FFFFFF`

### Prohibited Actions
- **NEVER** use custom colors outside the brand palette
- **NEVER** create color variations without explicit approval
- **NEVER** use non-brand colors for primary elements
- **NEVER** introduce alternative colors to the system

**Correct:**
```jsx
<button className="bg-primary text-white">Button</button>
<div className="bg-secondary text-primary">Section</div>
<div className="border-neutral">Border</div>
```

**Incorrect:**
```jsx
<button className="bg-blue-500">Button</button> // ❌ WRONG - not brand color
<div className="bg-[#FF5733]">Custom color</div> // ❌ WRONG - not in palette
```

### Color Usage Guidelines
- Use **Burgundy (primary)** for main brand elements, CTAs, and key highlights
- Use **Beige (secondary)** as complementary color for backgrounds
- Use **Cool Gray (neutral)** for balance, borders, and neutral elements
- Balance Burgundy and Beige usage over time

---

## TYPOGRAPHY SCALE RULES

### Display Sizes
- **MUST** use predefined display sizes for hero/display text:
  - `text-display-xl` (5.5rem)
  - `text-display-lg` (4.5rem)
  - `text-display-md` (3.5rem)
  - `text-display-sm` (2.5rem)
- **MUST** combine with `font-heading` for display text

**Correct:**
```jsx
<h1 className="font-heading text-display-xl">Hero Title</h1>
```

### Heading Sizes
- **MUST** use standard heading sizes (text-4xl, text-3xl, text-2xl, etc.)
- **MUST** always include `font-heading` class

**Correct:**
```jsx
<h1 className="font-heading text-4xl">Page Title</h1>
<h2 className="font-heading text-3xl">Section</h2>
```

---

## SPACING SYSTEM RULES

- **MUST** use Tailwind's spacing scale (4px base unit)
- **MUST** maintain consistent spacing:
  - Sections: `py-12` to `py-24`
  - Components: `mb-6` to `mb-12`
  - Cards: `p-6` to `p-8`
  - Buttons: `px-6 py-3`

---

## COMPONENT STYLING RULES

### Buttons
- **MUST** use Montserrat font (`font-montserrat`)
- **MUST** use brand colors (primary, secondary, neutral)
- **MUST** follow button padding guidelines

**Correct:**
```jsx
<button className="bg-primary text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-montserrat font-medium">
  Button
</button>
```

### Cards
- **MUST** use Botera for card headings
- **MUST** use Montserrat for card body text
- **MUST** use brand colors

**Correct:**
```jsx
<div className="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg">
  <h3 className="font-heading text-xl mb-4">Card Title</h3>
  <p className="font-montserrat">Card content</p>
</div>
```

---

## MANDATORY CHECKLIST

Before generating ANY code that involves styling, design, or UI:

- [ ] Have I read the relevant sections of `ORBIT_STYLE_GUIDE.md`?
- [ ] Is all English text using `font-heading`, `font-gotham`, or default sans (Gotham)?
- [ ] Is all Arabic/RTL text using `font-somar`?
- [ ] Are all colors from the brand palette (primary, secondary, neutral)?
- [ ] Have I avoided custom colors outside the palette?
- [ ] Does the spacing follow the guidelines?
- [ ] Are typography sizes appropriate for the element type?

---

## ENFORCEMENT

**These rules are MANDATORY and NON-NEGOTIABLE.**

When generating code:
1. **ALWAYS** check the style guide first
2. **ALWAYS** use the correct font families
3. **ALWAYS** use brand colors only
4. **ALWAYS** cite style guide sections when making design choices
5. **NEVER** deviate from these rules without explicit user approval

If you're unsure about any design decision:
1. Reference `ORBIT_STYLE_GUIDE.md`
2. Follow the guidelines exactly
3. Ask the user for clarification only if the style guide doesn't cover the specific case

---

## BRAND NAME

- **ALWAYS** refer to the brand as "ORBIT"
- **NEVER** use "MarkLine" or any other brand name
- **NEVER** reference old branding in new code

